title: Memoirs, part 1
author: jakemeister123
pages:
#- Jakemeister123's memoirs

A long time ago, I stumbled across these lands, known as civcraft. These lands housed many a city, which gave their people the needs to survive. My first city I stumbled across was Carbon. The people of Carbon 
#- were nice and friendly. They gave me a home, and the means to provide for myself. The people of Carbon were among the nicest I have ever met. Such people include 
Noir Wolf          Draziw
Kickalll             CarSowrd (pandaaa)
Wanado144    R3NNYB
#- And those are just to name a few.

Anyhow, back to the story. I was quite good friends with Vale (once known as Nexus) as I often made trades for xp items, and they often spoke with Carbon. In particular, snorriandgotrek would often come into the 
#- mumble to speak to us. One afternoon I was in Fellowship, delivering some goods, when snorriandgotrek invited me to live in Vale. This was during the time when NoirWolf and Draziw were leaving, and were taking the whole town with them. I knew that Carbon 
#- was never going to be the active, thriving city I once knew it to be. It was too good an offer to refuse. I took it. I packed my stuff, and started working on a house. Now, Nexus(Vale) might of been known for collaborating, but they are some of the nicest
#- people on the server, and I believe they are also the closest on the server. Vale = family
Yes they bickered, but doesn't mean they didn't treat each other as family.

Once I got settled into Vale, it is the most fun I have ever had on this server. 
#- Not to mention the means for gaining wealth, we did a lot of fun activities, and the mumble is often thriving. For example, jezza's photoshops are a work of art. 

I once saw some people fighting on civ pvp, and I thought that looked pretty neat.
#- So, I started training. First against civ people, then moving on to Kohi people. I was getting better every day, and now, I am probably one of the best fighters on civ, a very small percentage of people on civ can beat me. Never have I thought of using
#- these skills for bad. Now, I would name names of people in Vale who deserve proper mentions.
#- 